Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: JLRE is a boutique-style real estate company in South Boston, MA that differs from the standard brokerage in several ways. They are selective, they are fashionable, they are pet friendly and they are contemporary. They know the best—and not just the best properties, they know the best dry cleaners to the best butchers to the best coffee shops to the best restaurants. JLRE will be your one-stop information resource for the who, what, when and where in your new neighborhood. At Joyce Lebedew Real Estate, they pride ourselves on being more than just a real estate agency. They are part of a community, one that they not only love, but one that they grew up in as well. Their goal goes above and beyond simply helping people to buy, sell or rent a home; they strive to make their clients feel at home in South Boston as well.Here at JLRE, they sell what they know, what they love and where they would live ourselves. They know South Boston inside and out, they know the South Boston real estate market inside and out, and they share their deep understanding of the local South Boston neighborhoods with you so that your home purchase is aligned with your lifestyle, tastes and preferences. They have never and will never sell simply to sell. They have been known to talk clients out of a purchase that they know from engaging with them is not the right fit. Joyce Lebedew Real Estate is founded on the belief that each and every one of their clients should have the satisfaction, joy and peace of mind that what they are selling, buying or renting is right for them and is being handled by capable and qualified people. They know how stressful the selling or buying of a home can be and that sometimes it can be hard to see the light at the end of the tunnel. They also know that with the Joyce Lebedew team on your side, the process will go more smoothly and your level of stress and anxiety will be lessened. They have an incredible network of service providers that can help you with home improvement projects – from carpenters and plumbers to plasterers and electricians. These are people that they have longstanding relationships with and that they know and trust. Like us, they are vested in their community.
